Description: Arrow head of a reddish translucent stone, tip is broken off, the part to which the shaft would have been attached ends in a concave edge with two elongated parts left and right of it.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), West of town area, surface
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 142)
